f Varoma tray. Rinse mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl. Set Varoma in position and steam <b>35 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set puddings aside and allow to cool slightly (approx. 30 minutes). Serve warm or cold, drizzled with raspberry coulis and garnished with fresh berries."}],"hintsAndTricks":["The puddings can be steamed in other small dishes or containers, such as dariole moulds, espresso cups, glasses, verrines or silicone muffin cups, provided they are heatproof. Steaming time may need increasing by <b>5-10 minutes<b> if the containers are larger than <b>140 ml<b> each. If using ramekins or moulds no taller than <b>4 cm,<b> place them in both the Varoma dish and tray as described in the recipe. If using taller moulds, place them in Varoma dish and if they don’t all fit, steam them in <b>2 batches,<b> adding water as needed to mixing bowl.<br>- Leftover puddings can be stored in the fridge for <b>2-3 days.<b> Once steamed, allow puddings to cool to room temperature, then cover and refrigerate. Serve cold, or warm the puddings before serving by steaming in the simmering basket or Varoma above <b>400 g<b> water <b><strong>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1.<\/strong><b>","<i>These puddings could be breakfast, dessert or an after-school snack. However you choose to serve them, they are bursting with delicious and nutritious ingredients.<\/i>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h","6 portions"]}